SIMPLE: guacharo
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Guacharo
<hw>Gua*cha"ro</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Sp.
<ets>gu⟦aacute⟧charo</ets> sickly, dropsical, <ets>guacharaca</ets> a
sort of bird.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A nocturnal bird of South
America and Trinidad (<spn>Steatornis Caripensis</spn>, or <spn>S.
steatornis</spn>); -- called also <altname>oilbird</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It resembles the goatsuckers and nighthawks, but feeds
on fruits, and nests in caverns. A pure oil, used in place of butter, is
extracted from the young by the natives.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guacho</ent>⟦br⟧
